s","Hyperparathyroidism","Hyperthyroidism","Hypothyroidism"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDiabetes mellitus\u003C/strong\u003E commonly causes malabsorption through autonomic neuropathy, which affects gastrointestinal motility and can lead to bacterial overgrowth syndrome. While \u003Cstrong\u003Ehyperthyroidism\u003C/strong\u003E typically causes diarrhoea and increased transit time, it does not typically cause significant malabsorption. \u003Cstrong\u003EHypothyroidism\u003C/strong\u003E can slow gut motility but rarely causes malabsorption. \u003Cstrong\u003EHyperparathyroidism\u003C/strong\u003E primarily affects calcium metabolism but does not significantly impact nutrient absorption. \u003Cstrong\u003EAddison disease\u003C/strong\u003E can affect electrolyte balance but is not a primary cause of malabsorption.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Diabetes mellitus can cause malabsorption through autonomic neuropathy affecting gut motility","Endocrine disorders affecting the gastrointestinal system can lead to malabsorption through various mechanisms including altered motility and enzyme secretion"],"references":["Milman N. Intestinal absorption of folic acid - new physiologic \u0026 molecular aspects. Indian J Med Res. 2012 Nov;136(5):725-8. PMID: 23287118; PMCID: PMC3573592","Thomson AB, Keelan M, Thiesen A, Clandinin MT, Ropeleski M, Wild GE. Small bowel review: diseases of the small intestine. Dig Dis Sci. 2001 Dec;46(12):2555-66. doi: 10.1023/a:1012782321827. PMID: 11768246","Gu\u00e9ant JL, Gu\u00e9ant-Rodriguez RM, Alpers DH. Vitamin B12 absorption and malabsorption. Vitam Horm. 2022;119:241-274. doi: 10.1016/bs.vh.2022.01.016. Epub 2022 Mar 1. PMID: 35337622","Basile EJ, Launico MV, Sheer AJ. Physiology, Nutrient Absorption. [Updated 2023 Oct 28]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.n